title.narrative: By 2021, the participation of adolescents will be included in bodies and mechanisms for the management of health services andeducation, in addition to the corresponding quality indicators, for the priority territories.

description.narrative: 22,000 adolescents were engaged in citizen participation and civic activities with UNICEF&39;s support, including preparation of CRC report and consultations on climate change. One national and six local and regional adolescent participation networks were consolidated, allowing adolescents to share their voices with stakeholders and advocate to consider their ideas and proposals in management plans. UNICEF-supported the MINEDU consultation on the National Educational Emergency Plan to face the COVID-19 crisis with students. Overall, the UNICEF support to include the voice of adolescents in 4 regions, through the CONNA, reached more than 1 million children and adolescents of those areas indirectly. | Status:Met | As-of Date:22/12/2021
